'''Lake Como''' ([[Wikipedia:Italian language|Italian]]:Lago di Como) is a lake of [[Wikipedia:Glacier|glacial]] origin in [[Wikipedia:Lombardy|Lombardy]], [[Wikipedia:Italy|Italy]]. It has an area of 146 km², making it the third largest lake in Italy. At 410 m deep it is one of the deepest lakes in [[Wikipedia:Europe|Europe]] and the bottom of the lake is more than 200 meters below sea-level.

Three locations were filmed for [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Attack of the Clones'']] in Lake Como; [[Villa del Balbianello]], Tremezzo public garden and Picnic meadow, but the Tremezzo public garden was cut in the final edit. All three sequences show [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] and [[Padmé Amidala/Legends|Padmé Amidala]] at [[Varykino/Legends|Varykino]] on [[Naboo/Legends|Naboo]]. The filming took place on the first week of [[September]] [[2000]] and lasted four days.

